weekend tours central nigeria unmasked arts of the benue river valley events at stanford weekend tours central nigeria unmasked arts of the benue river valley facebook twitter email print add to calendar the benue river valley is the source of some of the most abstract dramatic and inventive art works in sub saharan africa this exhibition organized by the fowler museum at ucla is the first major view of the spectacular sculpture ceramic objects and video material representing the major artistic genres defining the lower middle and upper sub regions of the benue river valley starting at its confluence with the niger river and following eastward to its upper reaches around the gongola river its major tributary when ongoing every weekend sat sun from may 19 2012 through september 2 2012 2 00 pm approximate duration of 1 hour s where cantor arts center just off palm drive at museum way and lomita drive map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags arts international tour contact 723 4177 admission tours every thursday at 12 15 pm and saturday and sunday at 2 pm tours do not require a reservation call 723 3469 for large groups groups meet in the main museum lobby admission is free permalink http events stanford edu events 299 29957 last modified january 31 2012
